Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper introduces a new pooling method for sets of feature vectors to improve the flexibility of deep neural networks for sets. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed method on a set version of MNIST and CLEVR, which are commonly used datasets in computer vision. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new method for learning representations of sets, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new method for pooling feature vectors in deep neural networks for sets. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper mentions the use of the proposed method in constructing a permutation-equivariant auto-encoder, which is relevant to natural language processing tasks such as sentence classification.
